## 🧠 PHASE 0 — Before EC2 (Don’t skip)
✅ You must confirm locally:

Run Docker locally with ONLY:
- AuthService
- CoreService
- Nginx

👉 No frontend
👉 No Redis

Test:
\curl http://localhost/api/auth/health\
\curl http://localhost/api/core/health\

If this fails → don’t go to AWS yet

## ⚙️ PHASE 1 — Prepare Backend Images

**Step 1: Build .NET services**
\dotnet publish -c Release\
Do for:
- AuthService
- CoreService

**Step 2: Create Dockerfile (same for both)**
\\\dockerfile
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:8.0-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
ENV ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://+:80
EXPOSE 80
ENTRYPOINT ["dotnet", "YourService.dll"]
\\\

**Step 3: Build images**
\\\ash
docker build -t authservice .
docker build -t coreservice .
\\\

**Step 4: Save images**
\\\ash
docker save authservice -o authservice.tar
docker save coreservice -o coreservice.tar
\\\

## ☁️ PHASE 2 — Setup EC2

**Step 1: Create EC2**
- Instance: t2.micro
- OS: Ubuntu 22.04
- Storage: 20GB
- Open ports: 22 (SSH), 80 (HTTP), 443 (HTTPS)

**Step 2: Connect**
\ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@YOUR_IP\

**Step 3: Install Docker**
\\\ash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io docker-compose -y
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu
\\\
*Reconnect after this.*

## 📦 PHASE 3 — Upload & Load Images

**From your local machine:**
\\\ash
scp -i key.pem authservice.tar ubuntu@YOUR_IP:/home/ubuntu/
scp -i key.pem coreservice.tar ubuntu@YOUR_IP:/home/ubuntu/
\\\

**On EC2:**
\\\ash
docker load -i authservice.tar
docker load -i coreservice.tar
\\\

## ⚙️ PHASE 4 — docker-compose.yml

Create this:
\\\yaml
version: '3.8'

services:
  authservice:
    image: authservice
    ports:
      - "3001:80"
    environment:
      ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection: "YOUR_DB"
      ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT: "Production"
    restart: unless-stopped
    mem_limit: 300m

  coreservice:
    image: coreservice
    ports:
      - "3002:80"
    environment:
      ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection: "YOUR_DB"
      ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT: "Production"
    restart: unless-stopped
    mem_limit: 300m

  nginx:
    image: nginx:alpine
    ports:
      - "80:80"
    volumes:
      - "./nginx.conf:/etc/nginx/nginx.conf:ro"
    depends_on:
      - authservice
      - coreservice
    restart: unless-stopped
\\\

## 🌐 PHASE 5 — Nginx Config

Create \
ginx.conf\:
\\\
ginx
events {}

http {
    server {
        listen 80;

        location /api/auth/ {
            proxy_pass http://authservice/api/auth/;
        }

        location /api/core/ {
            proxy_pass http://coreservice/api/core/;
        }
    }
}
\\\

## ▶️ PHASE 6 — Start Everything
\docker-compose up -d\

Check:
\docker ps\

Test:
\curl http://YOUR_EC2_IP/api/auth/health\
👉 If this works → backend is LIVE

## 🌍 PHASE 7 — Connect Vercel

In Vercel Environment variables:
\NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://YOUR_EC2_IP\

